.SH NAME
dotty-env-get - Print a credential value.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdotty env get  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Print the value of a single credential to stdout. The argument is either a
KEY in the --namespace, or a full dotty:/// reference (which
names its own namespace). A trailing newline is printed unless --no-newline.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for get

.PP
\fB--no-newline\fP[=false]
	do not print a trailing newline


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--namespace\fP="default"
	credential namespace to operate on

.PP
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile to operate on (defaults to the active profile)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dotty env get --namespace=aws AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID
  dotty env get dotty://aws/AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID | pbcopy
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdotty-env(1)\fP
